@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{b}Introduction@{ub}
 MUIUploaderX is a File Uploader for Xenolink BBS Systems. I programmed it, because I wanted to learn programming GUI's for the Amiga and because IMHO Xenolink lacks GUI utilities.

 @{b}Features@{ub}
 - Aminet .readme support.
 - FileID support.
 - bulk uploading (NYI)
 - Moves/Copies the file to the correct direcory when uploading.
 - A nice Status Field.
 - Uses MUI ;)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

 @{b}Hardware Requirements@{ub}
 - Amiga Computer with a minimum of 1MB RAM

 @{b}Needed Software@{ub}
 - Kickstart 2.04 or higher
 - Xenolink BBS v1.984 or higher
 - MUI v3.3 or higher
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Registering" "Registering"

 @{b}Registering@{ub}
 Foold you ;) MUIUploaderX is called 'XenoWare'; that means that @{b}ONLY@{ub} Registerd Xenolink Sysops are allowed to use this product. Although a nice donation never hurts.
@ENDNODE

