@NODE "Installation" "Installation"

 @{b}Installationn@{ub}
 Drag the MUIUploaderX drawer to the destination device and configure the tooltypes.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ToolTypes" "Tooltypes"

 @{b}Tooltypes@{ub}
 MUIUploaderX knows five tooltypes. All the tooltypes has to be set correctly to fully use MUIUploaderX. The following Tooltypes are known by MUIUploaderX:

   - EDITOR = (AmigaDOS External Editor Command)
   - FILEID = (AmigaDOS FILEID Command)
   - DEFAULTDIR = (Default Directory)
   - FILE = (0=MOVE, 1=COPY)
   - DESCRIPTION = (0=NONE, 1=AMINET, 2=FILEID)

  eg.
       +-----------------------------------+
       |  EDITOR = ED -sicky               |
       |  FILEID = dldiz NH                |
       |  DEFAULTDIR = Xenolink:NewFiles/  |
       |  FILE = 0                         |
       |  DESCRIPTION = 1                  |
       +-----------------------------------+  
@ENDNODE

